-------------------------------------------------------------------------
                       2. THE BANANA OBLIGATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Before (or upon) using this software, you must fulfill the Banana
Obligation that matches your purpose:

  (a) COMMERCIAL USE
      Anyone using this software with commercial intent (selling it,
      using it in a paid product/service, or otherwise to make money)
      MUST open an Issue in the project's repository containing a
      photograph of SEVEN (7) real bananas. Each of the seven bananas
      must be clearly and individually NUMBERED 1 through 7 using paper
      notes or stickers visible in the photo. Only after this Issue is
      posted is commercial use permitted.

  (b) EDUCATIONAL OR PRIVATE USE
      Anyone using this software for educational, academic, hobby or
      otherwise private (non-commercial) purposes MUST, instead of the
      seven bananas, DRAW a picture of a single banana (one banana).
      The drawing may be shared as an Issue, in their fork's README, or
      kept with the project files. Stick figures of bananas are welcome.

These obligations are mandatory but deliberately silly. They exist to
make people smile and to acknowledge the banana-powered origins of this
software.

